\href{current_web_home_dir/AB_mP32_14_4e_4e-002}{Realgar ($B_{l}$)} transforms to pararealgar on exposure to visible light with wavelengths in the range 500-670\,nm. (Douglass, 1992) 
 \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_mP32_14_4e_4e-002}{Realgar (AsS, $B_{l}$)}, \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_mP32_14_4e_4e-001}{pararealgar (AsS)}, \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_mP32_14_4e_4e-004}{NS}, and \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_mP32_14_4e_4e-003}{NaGe} all have the same AFLOW prototype label, AB\_mP32\_14\_4e\_4e. They are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files.
